robot tests/smoke_tests.robot

Suppose you have:

File 1: tests/smoke_tests.robot

File 2: tests/regression_tests.robot

File 3: tests/api/critical_api.robot

robot tests/smoke_tests.robot tests/regression_tests.robot tests/api/critical_api.robot

robot tests/
This command executes every .robot test file inside the tests folder and its subdirectories at once.

Split execution to suite files:

pabot [path to tests]

Split execution on test level:

pabot --testlevelsplit [path to tests]

Run with 8 parallel processes:

pabot --processes 8 [path to tests]
